BT 0 g /F2 14 Tf 185.04000000000002 740 Td (HOW ACCOMMODATION MAKES ANXIETY GROW) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 50 730 m 562 730 l S Q
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 50 705 Td (ACCOMMODATION = changing YOUR behavior to reduce your child's anxiety.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 50 680 Td (Examples:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 660 Td (- Letting them stay home from school because they're anxious) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 644 Td (- Speaking for them so they don't have to) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 628 Td (- Sleeping in their room every night) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 612 Td (- Avoiding all situations that trigger their anxiety) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 596 Td (- Answering the same reassurance question 20 times) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 580 Td (- Doing things for them they could do \(ordering food, etc.\)) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 50 554 Td (WHY THIS BACKFIRES:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 534 Td (- It teaches: 'You CAN'T handle this' \(confirms their fear\)) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 518 Td (- It prevents them from learning they CAN cope) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 502 Td (- Anxiety's world shrinks - needs MORE accommodation over time) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 486 Td (- It's exhausting for the whole family) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 50 455 Td (MY CURRENT ACCOMMODATIONS \(be honest\):) Tj ET
q 0.7 G 0.5 w 60 435 m 540 435 l S Q
q 0.7 G 0.5 w 60 415 m 540 415 l S Q
q 0.7 G 0.5 w 60 395 m 540 395 l S Q
q 0.7 G 0.5 w 60 375 m 540 375 l S Q

endstream
endobj
