BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 236.88 740 Td (THE BRAVE APPROACH) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 50 730 m 562 730 l S Q
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 50 705 Td (Gradual exposure helps your child learn they CAN handle hard things.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 60 680 Td (B - Be understanding:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 664 Td (Validate their feelings first. 'I see you're scared.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 60 640 Td (R - Reduce accommodation:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 624 Td (Gradually stop doing things that maintain anxiety.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 60 600 Td (A - Approach the fear:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 584 Td (Help them face fears in small steps \(exposure ladder\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 60 560 Td (V - Validate courage:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 544 Td ('That was hard and you did it!' Praise bravery.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 60 520 Td (E - Expect setbacks:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 504 Td (Progress isn't linear. Bad days don't erase progress.) Tj ET
BT 0.3 g /F2 10 Tf 50 480 Td (KEY PRINCIPLE: Your child needs to FEEL the anxiety and learn it passes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 460 Td (We can't remove all anxiety. We can build their confidence to cope.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
