BT 0 g /F2 14 Tf 215.28 740 Td (SCRIPTS FOR ANXIOUS MOMENTS) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 50 730 m 562 730 l S Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 50 710 Td (What to SAY \(and not say\) when your child is anxious:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 55 685 Td (INSTEAD OF: 'There's nothing to worry about.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F5 9 Tf 55 671 Td (TRY: 'I see you're worried. What's your brain telling you?') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 55 647 Td (INSTEAD OF: 'You'll be fine, stop being silly.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F5 9 Tf 55 633 Td (TRY: 'This feels hard right now. I believe you can do hard things.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 55 609 Td (INSTEAD OF: 'Okay, you don't have to go.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F5 9 Tf 55 595 Td (TRY: 'I know you're scared. Let's figure out how to do this together.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 55 571 Td (INSTEAD OF: 'What's wrong with you?') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F5 9 Tf 55 557 Td (TRY: 'Your worry brain is being loud today. What can we do?') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 50 528 Td (UNIVERSAL SCRIPTS:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 60 511 Td ('I'm right here with you.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 60 496 Td ('Your brain is sending a false alarm. You're safe.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 60 481 Td ('What's the worst that could happen? Could you handle it?') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 60 466 Td ('Remember when you were scared of ___ and you did it anyway?') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 60 451 Td ('I love you AND I know you can do this.') Tj ET

endstream
endobj
